Mexican Stocks: Grupo Mexico, Industrias Penoles, Minera Frisco

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-05-05T21:06:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/mexican-stocks-grupo-mexico-industrias-penoles-minera-frisco.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index declined for the fourth day, slipping 0.6
percent to 35,325.09, as commodities prices tumbled. The Thomson
Reuters/Jefferies CRB Index of 19 raw materials fell 4.9 percent
to 341.07.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, tumbled 2.1 percent to 38 pesos. Copper for July
delivery lost as much as 16.95 cents, or 4.1 percent, to $3.9645
a pound on the Comex in New York.  Silver futures for July delivery fell as much as $5.138, or
13 percent, to $34.25 an ounce on the Comex in New York.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, declined 4 percent to 395.47 pesos. Minera
Frisco SAB (MFRISCOA MM), the mining company controlled by
billionaire  Carlos Slim , retreated 1.4 percent to 46.66 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  